result.execSummary:
The defendant Cassie Jean Gutierrez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant shall not possess or consume any controlled substance, unless it is prescribed to them as medication by his or her physician.

Defendant shall agree to random drug testing ordered by John Shulta.  
Defendant shall not have any direct or indirect contact with Audrey Clancey, Tacoa Talley and Deiante Jones.  Contact includes: contact at petitioner home, work, school, public places, in person, by phone, in writing, by electronic communication or device, or in any other manner.
Defendant shall not leave the State of Wisconsin except for court appearances in the State of Iowa.

03:39 PM Defendant Cassie Jean Gutierrez appeared with Atty Adam Witt by video means. Prosecuting Atty Jenna L Gill appeared for State of Wisconsin.

Defendant and Atty Witt acknowledge receipt of the complaint and waive reading.
Court finds complaint states probable cause.
State informs Court that defendant has a pending felony case in the State of Iowa and requests $1,000.00 cash bail with conditions:
- no possession or consumption of controlled substances...
- no contact with individuals names in criminal complaint, Audrey Clancey, Tacoa Talley, Deiante Jones
Recess taken to allow Atty Witt to speak with defendant.  Back in session at 3:50 p.m.
Atty Witt believes defendant will qualify for P.D. representation; her residence is in the City of Darlington and believes that future appearances will not be a problem; requests signature bond and does not oppose the requested conditions.
State is concerned about contact with a nephew who may reside with the defendant because of the possession of meth.
Court orders $2,000.00 signature bond with conditions:
- no contact with the Audrey Clancey, Tacoa Talley, Deiante Jones
- no posession or consumption of controlled substances without prescription
- subject to randaom drug testing/bail monitoring with John Shulta
- shall not leave the State of Wisconsin except for court appearances in the State of Iowa
Defendant waives time limits for setting preliminary hearing.
Set for adjourned initial appearance 2/28/21 at 1:00 p.m.
